The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | New Speaker elected
                                                                                                               New Speaker elected
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Bhubaneswar, May 25: BJD legislator from Boudh and former steel and mines minister Pradip Kumar Amat was elected unanimously as the Speaker of the newly-constituted Assembly.         
	Todays election was a formality as the ruling BJD commands an absolute majority (103 seats) in the 147-member Assembly.         
	Amat was elected as the 18th Speaker, following Kishore Kumar Mohanty, who was defeated in the recent Assembly polls.        
	At the outset of the especially convened session today, chief minister and leader of the House Naveen Patnaik moved a motion proposing Amats election and was seconded by parliamentary affairs minister Raghunath Mohanty.         
	Moving the motion, Naveen said Amat, who has been getting elected to the Assembly from Boudh constituency since 2000, has distinguished himself thanks to his performance on the floor of the House.         
	Protem Speaker V. Sugyan Kumari Deo declared Amat as elected after the motion was adopted by voice vote.         
	Im confident that with his vast legislative experience Amat will perform his duties with dignity, said the veteran Deo, who has been elected to the Assembly nine times.        
	Leader of Opposition Bhupinder Singh hoped that Amat, who was elected unanimously, would be impartial and give an opportunity to all, especially 68 first-timers, to participate in the proceedings.         
	The newly elected Speaker was congratulated by the chief minister, NCP leader Prasant Nanda and BJP leader K.V. Singhdeo. Thanking members, Amat said upholding the dignity of the House would be his priority and sought their co-operation in this regard.                                                                                                                                                                           
